article.headline: Lehigh 37, Yale 7
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- Lehigh overcame four turnovers, with Chris Lum passing for three touchdowns in a 37-7 win over Yale on Saturday. The Mountain Hawks (4-1) led 10-7 before Lum heated up with three straight touchdown passes over a 20-minute span as the lead grew to 30-7. Lum was 34 of 46 for 378 yards passing with two interceptions. He has thrown for at least 300 yards in six straight games, dating back to last season. Jake Drwal caught all three touchdown passes and finished with 10 receptions for 112 yards. Ryan Spadola caught 11 passes for 148 yards. Lehigh's defense created havoc for Yale all day. The Bulldogs (2-1) turned the ball over five times and were held to only 83 yards on 30 carries. Lehigh registered a season-high four sacks and had eight tackles for loss. Deon Randall scored Yale's only touchdown on an 8-yard pass from Patrick Witt.
